1
00:01:45,319 --> 00:01:45,840
Come.

2
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,200
Little Wu.

3
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:55,439
Uncle.

4
00:01:59,840 --> 00:02:00,719
You’re such a sweet talker.

5
00:02:00,719 --> 00:02:01,840
Who’s this?

6
00:02:03,879 --> 00:02:04,280
Sis.

7
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:05,920
You came back out of the blue and startled me.

8
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:06,719
Little Wu.

9
00:02:06,719 --> 00:02:07,280
Sis.

10
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:09,680
This is my son.

11
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:10,560
Call her Aunt.

12
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:11,479
Aunt.

13
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:14,159
Give me a hug.

14
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:15,879
What should he call you?

15
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:17,080
Kid.

16
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,960
He’s really good-looking.

17
00:02:19,439 --> 00:02:19,879
Sis.

18
00:02:20,199 --> 00:02:20,639
You came at this hour.

19
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:21,719
Hope I’m not interrupting your business.

20
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:22,960
Not at all.

21
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:23,639
Let’s go.

22
00:02:23,919 --> 00:02:24,879
Let’s go to Aunt’s room.

23
00:02:24,879 --> 00:02:26,280
Come on, let’s go to Aunt’s room.

24
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:28,759
Uncle.

25
00:02:29,759 --> 00:02:30,280
Kid.

26
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:31,280
Come here.

27
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:36,639
Take this and eat.

28
00:02:37,840 --> 00:02:38,560
Thank you, Uncle.

29
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:39,599
You’re welcome.

30
00:02:40,759 --> 00:02:41,280
Sis.

31
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:42,960
What’s going on in town?

32
00:02:43,159 --> 00:02:44,080
It’s so quiet.

33
00:02:45,479 --> 00:02:46,639
Isn’t it because of the Japanese trouble?

34
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:48,199
It’s the same everywhere.

35
00:02:50,039 --> 00:02:51,319
No one’s by the river anymore.

36
00:02:52,919 --> 00:02:53,400
What?

37
00:02:54,879 --> 00:02:56,000
Did you go back to check?

38
00:02:57,719 --> 00:02:58,520
Just passed by.

39
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:02,759
These past few years,

40
00:03:03,039 --> 00:03:04,199
no one dares to go there.

41
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,360
Those making a living at the border,

42
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:07,080
the ginseng gatherers,

43
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:08,240
herb pickers and lumberjacks,

44
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:09,080
all avoid that place.

45
00:03:09,879 --> 00:03:11,080
Timber rafters can’t avoid it,

46
00:03:11,639 --> 00:03:12,639
but even they go less often now.

47
00:03:13,680 --> 00:03:14,879
Those who lived dangerously are gone.

48
00:03:14,919 --> 00:03:15,800
No more hosting guests.

49
00:03:16,319 --> 00:03:18,039
Everyone who should leave has left.

50
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,639
What about my second and third sisters?

51
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:23,000
The year after you left,

52
00:03:23,759 --> 00:03:25,319
your second sister went to the back hills.

53
00:03:26,159 --> 00:03:27,080
And your third sister?

54
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:27,719
She went with someone.

55
00:03:27,719 --> 00:03:28,719
She left with a border worker.

56
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,319
They all had hard lives.

57
00:03:31,199 --> 00:03:31,759
Not many

58
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:32,919
are as fortunate as you.

59
00:03:33,919 --> 00:03:35,159
The newcomers,

60
00:03:35,759 --> 00:03:37,120
they’re all wary of each other.

61
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:39,319
Can’t look after both sides.

62
00:03:40,639 --> 00:03:41,719
Like the fast northern current,

63
00:03:42,039 --> 00:03:42,879
just passing by.

64
00:03:44,439 --> 00:03:45,639
It’s nothing like it used to be.

65
00:03:52,879 --> 00:03:53,360
Sis,

66
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:54,960
How are you doing?

67
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:56,680
Still managing on your own?

68
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:57,960
Not looking for someone?

69
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:02,879
I'm not talking about myself, I'm talking about you.

70
00:04:03,479 --> 00:04:04,919
Did you come back just to visit this time,

71
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,319
or is there something going on?

72
00:04:08,479 --> 00:04:09,439
To be honest with you, sis,

73
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:12,120
my husband ran into some trouble.

74
00:04:12,719 --> 00:04:13,599
We're worried something might go wrong.

75
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:15,039
So he let me and our child

76
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:16,079
come back and hide out for a few days.

77
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:17,399
Once things settle down,

78
00:04:17,759 --> 00:04:18,560
he'll come pick us up.

79
00:04:19,879 --> 00:04:20,680
No matter what happens,

80
00:04:21,639 --> 00:04:23,920
just stay safe here at home.

81
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,639
We both saw it with our own eyes.

82
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,240
There really were agents pretending to be customers.

83
00:04:30,279 --> 00:04:31,720
They left the restaurant and followed Fuqing.

84
00:04:32,160 --> 00:04:33,240
After we shook them off,

85
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:34,079
they went to the Tokkō.

86
00:04:34,439 --> 00:04:35,160
Waiting to report back.

87
00:04:35,759 --> 00:04:36,759
Didn't expect so many people

88
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:37,519
were watching that place.

89
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:40,199
No wonder Old Tang didn't dare talk to us.

90
00:04:41,319 --> 00:04:41,759
Also,

91
00:04:42,519 --> 00:04:43,360
at Old Tang's restaurant,

92
00:04:43,399 --> 00:04:44,399
the boss Tian who was eating there

93
00:04:44,879 --> 00:04:45,680
was actually Morita.

94
00:04:46,439 --> 00:04:47,720
He also went to the Tokkō later.

95
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:48,480
That's right.

96
00:04:48,839 --> 00:04:49,560
If you ask me,

97
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:51,439
we should take care of Morita first.

98
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:52,160
Get rid of him.

99
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,040
Then we'll see

100
00:04:54,959 --> 00:04:56,079
if Old Tang will still work with us.

101
00:04:56,079 --> 00:04:56,759
Stop dilly-dallying.

102
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:58,360
Even if we take out Morita,

103
00:04:58,360 --> 00:04:59,920
other Japanese will come.

104
00:05:01,279 --> 00:05:02,480
Getting rid of Morita

105
00:05:04,439 --> 00:05:06,439
will definitely give Tang Deyuan

106
00:05:06,759 --> 00:05:07,680
a chance to breathe.

107
00:05:08,639 --> 00:05:10,000
Besides, Morita

108
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,680
has been targeting Xiao Tielin.

109
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:13,879
If we eliminate him,

110
00:05:14,519 --> 00:05:15,480
even if the Japanese

111
00:05:15,480 --> 00:05:16,480
send someone else over,

112
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:17,720
it'll take some time.

113
00:05:17,959 --> 00:05:18,920
By then, the police station

114
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,439
will be in total chaos.

115
00:05:21,199 --> 00:05:22,120
Maybe

116
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,240
that's our chance to go after Xiao Tielin.

117
00:05:24,279 --> 00:05:25,480
It's a good opportunity to strike.

118
00:05:27,199 --> 00:05:27,920
So what should we do?

119
00:05:28,079 --> 00:05:29,120
I'll disguise myself as a Japanese,

120
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,399
get close to Morita and take him out.

121
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,360
We've all shown our faces at the restaurant.

122
00:05:33,879 --> 00:05:34,839
We need someone new.

123
00:05:35,639 --> 00:05:38,560
I'll report this to our superiors.

124
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:51,439
Xiaogui,

125
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:53,839
Are you okay?

126
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,199
I'm fine.

127
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,639
I had a nightmare and my leg cramped.

128
00:06:00,319 --> 00:06:01,040
Are you really okay?

129
00:06:02,519 --> 00:06:04,160
I'm fine, Deyuan.

130
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:19,399
That's the whole situation.

131
00:06:20,079 --> 00:06:20,720
So,

132
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:22,759
I want to ask the organization

133
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:24,560
to help us out.

134
00:06:26,879 --> 00:06:27,480
Go ahead.

135
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:30,120
Eliminate Morita from the police station.

136
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:33,079
And this matter

137
00:06:33,959 --> 00:06:36,000
must not involve Tang Deyuan.

138
00:06:37,639 --> 00:06:38,519
Come again next time.

139
00:06:41,680 --> 00:06:42,399
Hello, sir.

140
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,439
We're closed now.

141
00:06:46,079 --> 00:06:46,600
Oh, it's you.

142
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:47,720
Please, come in.

143
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,680
You have a new mission.

144
00:07:27,279 --> 00:07:28,560
The man in the car is Morita.

145
00:07:29,319 --> 00:07:30,519
Figure out his routine.

146
00:07:31,639 --> 00:07:32,639
Find a chance to kill him.

147
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:35,560
Because of our recent actions,

148
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,519
a series of operations,

149
00:07:37,279 --> 00:07:38,519
they've become more cautious.

150
00:07:47,839 --> 00:07:48,720
Stay for two more days.

151
00:07:50,319 --> 00:07:51,480
Why stay here?

152
00:07:52,319 --> 00:07:53,560
It's not easy

153
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:54,560
to come all the way to Mudanjiang.

154
00:07:55,079 --> 00:07:56,800
I thought I'd show you around.

155
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,439
Isn't Harbin even bigger?

156
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,439
We should walk around both.

157
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:03,519
Is that okay?

158
00:08:03,639 --> 00:08:04,680
Sure, I like walking around.

159
00:08:13,839 --> 00:08:15,519
No, I need to go to the bathroom.

160
00:09:29,519 --> 00:09:30,120
Don't move.

161
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:30,879
Come with me.

162
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:36,600
Brother Yunhu.

163
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:38,080
Who’s your brother?

164
00:09:39,399 --> 00:09:41,120
I went to Tiantian Hao Da Restaurant to look for you.

165
00:09:41,559 --> 00:09:42,919
They said you’d already left.

166
00:09:43,759 --> 00:09:44,720
I want to ask you something.

167
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,360
Ask what?

168
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,000
Are you with the Northeast Anti-Japanese United Army?

169
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:54,720
What do you do?

170
00:09:55,399 --> 00:09:56,159
Who sent you here?

171
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:57,440
Looks like I guessed right.

172
00:09:57,559 --> 00:09:58,399
You didn’t guess anything.

173
00:09:58,919 --> 00:10:00,200
My real name is Liu Wanchun.

174
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,679
Comrade Han Guang sent me.

175
00:10:05,559 --> 00:10:06,320
Brother Yunhu.

176
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:08,399
I just saw you.

177
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:11,279
I really couldn’t leave just like that.

178
00:10:12,519 --> 00:10:13,399
So I thought,

179
00:10:13,759 --> 00:10:15,000
I’d take a risk and come ask you.

180
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,639
Then how did you know who I am?

181
00:10:18,200 --> 00:10:18,960
I’m with Xiaohongzao

182
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:19,879
in the same opera troupe.

183
00:10:20,559 --> 00:10:21,799
When she was chatting with me,

184
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,960
she mentioned what you did in Songlin Town.

185
00:10:24,759 --> 00:10:26,360
When I was at Tiantian Hao Da Restaurant

186
00:10:26,399 --> 00:10:27,240
performing,

187
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:28,360
I was also watching you.

188
00:10:28,720 --> 00:10:29,320
Plus,

189
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:30,840
you showed up in Mudanjiang

190
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:32,519
at that place and time.

191
00:10:33,759 --> 00:10:34,519
So I figured

192
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:35,840
you must be one of us.

193
00:10:46,919 --> 00:10:48,000
The Party Central Committee is in Yan'an.

194
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:49,519
It has already established

195
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,200
a special Northeast Work Committee.

196
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,159
At the Shanxi-Chahar-Hebei Bureau

197
00:10:53,159 --> 00:10:54,039
and the Shandong Bureau,

198
00:10:54,559 --> 00:10:55,559
they have also set up

199
00:10:55,639 --> 00:10:57,279
special Northeast Work Committees.

200
00:10:58,200 --> 00:10:59,399
Over the years, many people have been sent

201
00:10:59,399 --> 00:11:00,000
outside the pass

202
00:11:00,759 --> 00:11:02,120
to restore organizations and search for the Northeast Anti-Japanese United Army.

203
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:03,559
Comrade Han Guang

204
00:11:04,039 --> 00:11:05,120
is from the Shanxi-Chahar-Hebei Bureau

205
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:06,519
and is specifically in charge of Northeast affairs.

206
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:08,840
After I received the assignment,

207
00:11:08,879 --> 00:11:09,679
I came to the Northeast.

208
00:11:10,559 --> 00:11:11,960
I've been with the opera troupe for over two years.

209
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:13,759
Traveling all over the place,

210
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:15,360
looking for traces of the troops.

211
00:11:15,879 --> 00:11:16,759
Some time ago,

212
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:19,399
Comrade Han Guang received instructions from Yan'an

213
00:11:19,879 --> 00:11:21,159
to make sure I come to Mudanjiang

214
00:11:21,799 --> 00:11:22,960
and find the Northeast Anti-Japanese United Army.

215
00:11:23,399 --> 00:11:24,720
Then reestablish contact with Yan'an.

216
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:27,279
So how can you prove

217
00:11:27,279 --> 00:11:28,240
what you say is true?

218
00:11:30,039 --> 00:11:30,919
I can't prove it.

219
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:33,720
When I left the pass back then,

220
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:35,200
to avoid inspection,

221
00:11:35,799 --> 00:11:36,960
I burned all my documents.

222
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:39,559
Let me tell you,

223
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:41,639
the situation has changed now.

224
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:43,559
The Communist Party-led

225
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:45,240
Eighth Route Army and New Fourth Army

226
00:11:45,559 --> 00:11:46,960
have already launched local counterattacks.

227
00:11:47,879 --> 00:11:49,039
Besides attacking the Japanese puppet army's

228
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:50,480
weakly defended strongholds

229
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:51,639
and transportation lines,

230
00:11:51,759 --> 00:11:53,559
they are carrying out continuous offensive operations.

231
00:11:54,399 --> 00:11:55,679
They have also sent troops to the outer lines,

232
00:11:56,759 --> 00:11:57,639
advancing toward Henan,

233
00:11:58,240 --> 00:11:59,000
the Hunan-Guangdong border,

234
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:00,480
and the Jiangsu-Zhejiang-Anhui border.

235
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:02,240
Let me give you another good news.

236
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,159
Yan'an

237
00:12:04,519 --> 00:12:06,000
is holding the Party's Seventh National Congress.

238
00:12:06,799 --> 00:12:08,279
They are preparing for a major counteroffensive against Japan.

239
00:12:08,279 --> 00:12:08,919
Getting ready.

240
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,000
Organizationally,

241
00:12:11,679 --> 00:12:13,360
the Mudanjiang contact points provided

242
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:14,039
I've visited them all.

243
00:12:15,399 --> 00:12:17,360
The Xinyi Trading Company on Guanshe Street now

244
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:19,279
used to be called Dayou Trading Company.

245
00:12:19,919 --> 00:12:21,679
It was a contact place for the Northeast Anti-Japanese United Army comrades.

246
00:12:22,279 --> 00:12:23,039
It's been withdrawn.

247
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,039
You can verify this.

248
00:12:28,919 --> 00:12:30,519
Today, I caught a lead.

249
00:12:30,759 --> 00:12:32,240
He said he was acting on orders from Yan'an,

250
00:12:32,399 --> 00:12:33,639
sent by the Party organization inside the pass.

251
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:35,919
How did he target you?

252
00:12:40,399 --> 00:12:40,919
He

253
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,519
plays the banhu in an opera troupe.

254
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:44,080
There's a performer in that troupe

255
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:44,919
named Xiaohongzao.

256
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:46,039
I know her.

257
00:12:46,279 --> 00:12:47,440
She helped me in Songlin Town.

258
00:12:47,759 --> 00:12:48,879
He probably heard it from her.

259
00:12:50,039 --> 00:12:50,919
Opera troupe—

260
00:12:51,879 --> 00:12:53,679
that's a place full of all sorts of people.

261
00:12:53,840 --> 00:12:55,080
It's a good place to hide.

262
00:12:55,279 --> 00:12:55,720
Yes.

263
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:58,600
Eat.

264
00:12:58,960 --> 00:12:59,919
There's also red sausage.

265
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:01,039
It's hot.

266
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:06,639
He said,

267
00:13:07,879 --> 00:13:09,639
he was sent by Comrade Han Guang.

268
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:11,600
He came all the way from the Shanxi-Chahar-Hebei region

269
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:12,840
to Northeast China to find the Northeast Anti-Japanese United Army.

270
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:14,799
He even knew about

271
00:13:14,799 --> 00:13:15,960
the contact point we closed before.

272
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:16,879
Dayou Trading Company.

273
00:13:17,559 --> 00:13:18,639
And the way we exchanged information.

274
00:13:18,679 --> 00:13:19,679
He described it in great detail.

275
00:13:19,879 --> 00:13:20,799
I don't think he made it up.

276
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:24,039
So what did you agree with him?

277
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:26,720
I told him to go

278
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:27,679
wait for me at Anji Company tomorrow.

279
00:13:28,720 --> 00:13:29,039
Squad Leader,

280
00:13:29,039 --> 00:13:29,679
I know doing this

281
00:13:29,679 --> 00:13:30,399
is a bit risky.

282
00:13:30,639 --> 00:13:31,320
But haven't we always

283
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:31,919
been longing

284
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,320
